line_1: Crouching to earth his guileful pointer fawns,
line_2: Thro' greyish mists behold Aurora dawns,

line_1: And pursue with our eye the young fawns.
line_2: And checquer the meads, and the lawns,

line_1: Sweet babes, who, like the little playful fawns,
line_2: Were wont to trip along these verdant lawns

line_1: The Dryads, Satyrs, Silver Gods, and Fawns,
line_2: Had here their Rural Pallaces and Lawns.
